HEADWORD: Harmonist
<hw>Har"mo*nist</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r"m⟦osl⟧*n⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>harmoniste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
shows the agreement or harmony of corresponding passages of different
authors, as of the four evangelists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>One who understands the principles
of harmony or is skillful in applying them in composition; a musical
composer.</def></p>

<p><ent>Harmonite</ent>⟦br⟧
